subsection.def:
objector
                    (異議人) means a person who files a notice of
                objection under rule 26(2) or 55(1), as the case may be;

the
                    Ordinance
                    (本條例) means the Trade Marks Ordinance (Cap. 559);

send
                    (送交) includes give, and cognate expressions
                are to be construed accordingly;

paragraph.content:
the application contains a statement claiming the colour or colours as the
                    trade mark, or as an element or elements of the trade mark, as the case may be;
                    and

file written representations to establish that the
                                                  requirements for registration are met;
                                                  or

file written representations or further written
                                                  representations to establish that the requirements
                                                  for registration are met;

subparagraph.content:
the applicant needs additional time to
                                                  obtain the consent of the owner of a relevant
                                                  earlier trade mark;

paragraph.content:
if it is registered, a statement indicating the classes and
                                        the goods or services in respect of which it is
                                        registered;

amend the application as proposed by the applicant (if he is satisfied that
                    the proposed amendment complies with section 46 of the
                    Ordinance);

the date of registration as determined in accordance with section
                        48 of the Ordinance, that is to say, the filing date of the
                    application for registration;

the actual date of registration, that is to say, the date of the entry in
                    the register of the particulars required to be entered under this
                    rule;

where the trade mark or any element of the trade mark consists of a
                    3-dimensional shape for which a claim has been made in accordance with rule
                        6(2), that fact;

the revocation of the registration of a trade mark as a defensive trade
                    mark on the grounds mentioned in section 60(6) of the
                    Ordinance;

a declaration of invalidity of the registration of a collective mark on the
                    grounds mentioned in section 14 of Schedule 3 to the Ordinance;
                    or

state whether the registration is surrendered in respect of all of the
                    goods or services for which the trade mark is registered or in respect of only
                    certain of those goods or services;

where the registration is surrendered in respect of only certain goods or
                    services, specify the goods or services concerned by reference to their class or
                    classes in the International Classification;

subparagraph.content:
the name and address of the assignee;
                        (3 of 2020 s.
                        21)

paragraph.content:
an application for the revocation of the registration of a trade mark,
                    defensive trade mark, collective mark or certification mark under rule
                        40;

an application for a declaration of invalidity of the registration of a
                    trade mark, collective mark or certification mark under rule
                    46;

an application for the variation of the registration of a trade mark or for
                    the rectification of an error or omission in the register under rule
                        48;

rule 32(1) and
                        (3)
                    (time for renewing registration);

the trade marks in respect of which the application is made constitute a
                    series within the meaning of section 51(3) of the
                    Ordinance;

if he is satisfied that the opposition has merit, refuse to accept the
                    amendment;
                    or

a person whose name has been struck off the roll of barristers or roll of solicitors
        kept under and in accordance with the Legal Practitioners Ordinance (Cap. 159) or any person who has been suspended from acting as a barrister or
        solicitor;

a partnership or body corporate of which one of the partners or directors is a person
        whom the Registrar could refuse to recognize as an agent under paragraph (a) or
        (b);
